comment: Global offset is -1.4 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure. Printhead loose --> fixated with tape. GelMA (T1) and HAMA (T2). Vol. T1: 600 µL (layer 1), + ~400 µL (layer 3). Vol. T2: 600 µL (layer 2).  Washing channels: dipping, then rinsing 3x1 mL warm DPBS with pipette, removing excess liquid with KimWipe (touching channels). Store in warm ECGM2 until further use.  super prints, air bubble in first layer of one print --> position 6    Transferring all at the same time into separate 24-wells with 0.5 mL 2x Hase in ECGM2 +P/S (230120 MF ).     Note: no cells in GelMA, HUVECS and MSCs are mixed in equal parts into HAMA
